{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"620dc78f-30a3-4129-8fe1-893b4874bfaf","content":"Workflow created at `.github/workflows/publish.yml`. Here's how it works:\n\n**Workflow** — Triggers on version tags (`v*`). Builds & packs in one job, then publishes in a separate job with `id-token: write` permission. No API key needed — `dotnet nuget push` auto-authenticates via the OIDC token.\n\n**Manual step — Register the trusted publisher on nuget.org:**\n\n1. Go to **nuget.org → Manage Packages → Add a Trusted Publisher** (or configure it when first creating the package).\n2. Fill in:\n   - **Repository owner:** `myorg`\n   - **Repository name:** `mylib`\n   - **Workflow:** `publish.yml`\n   - **Environment:** *(leave blank)*\n3. Save.\n\n**To publish**, push a tag:\n```bash\ngit tag v1.0.0\ngit push origin v1.0.0\n```\n\nThe `publish` job uses the GitHub-issued OIDC token, and NuGet validates it against your registered trusted publisher — no secrets required.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"19ac0d0e-6aaa-48fd-83f2-ec8f9dc41152","outputTokens":257},"id":"11a4cd41-e9cd-4cc9-b909-1b53400b90cc","timestamp":"2026-04-05T00:42:06.749Z","parentId":"55facf05-3d9d-45dd-bef3-1307654042f9"}
